[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Escalation triggers]                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Milestone window exceeded                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-step coordination failure pattern              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient or caregiver explicit request for human      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Clinical concern outside coordinator scope           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Social-determinants concern requiring care           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      navigation                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health concern requiring routing              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Records-flow gap that the assistant cannot resolve   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-institutional dispute requiring human          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      negotiation                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot confidence below threshold                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver-burden signal indicating intervention      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Handoff targets]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active emergency: 911 with stay-on-the-line guidance │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Acute-symptom presentation: triage workflow          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (recipe 11.6)                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health concern: mental-health support         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (recipe 11.8) or 988                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Clinical concern: care team via institutional        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      messaging                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Coordination concern: institutional human            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      coordinator queue                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Social-determinants concern: care-navigation         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      workflow                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Warm-handoff payload]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent conversation transcript                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active journey and milestone state                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trigger reason and pattern                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's preferred contact method                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's stated preferences                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot's structured summary of the coordination problem │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bridge-and-stay pattern]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot does not just transfer the patient               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot bridges to human within the platform             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot stays present until human has joined             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient does not start over                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: handoff event with structured payload to       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    appropriate target, conversation continuity preserved] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND CROSS-SYSTEM CORRELATION ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated bot responses                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Action proposals and confirmations                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care-plan template version                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active journey-content-corpus version                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Cross-system event correlation]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from EHR (encounter, discharge, order,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      result)                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from referral system (referral created,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      acknowledged, scheduled, completed)                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from scheduling system (booked, confirmed,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      no-showed, rescheduled, cancelled)                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from records-release workflow (request, ack,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      fulfilled, gap)                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from pharmacy (fill, refill, gap)             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from durable-medical-equipment workflow       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (order, delivery, install)                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from home-health workflow (order, initial-    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      visit, ongoing-visits)                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Events from HIE (record received from external       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      source)                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Milestone-completion rate by journey type            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Records-flow completion rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-completion-within-window rate               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Appointment-attendance rate                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Coordinator-handoff rate                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Escalation conversion rate                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, journey type, social-         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      determinant flags)                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of escalations,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      action proposals, and low-confidence interactions    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (licensed nurses or care coordinators)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tag failure modes (out-of-scope, hallucinated-state, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      missed-escalation, scope-violation, citation-gap,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tone-failure, action-proposal-error)                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-plan-template-revision proposals]                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system orchestration as architectural primitive.** The assistant reads across the EHR, the referral system, the scheduling system, the records-release workflow, the pharmacy system, the HIE, and external-system reports. The unified view is the foundation; without it the assistant is a chatbot, not a coordinator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-plan-as-code with milestone decomposition.** Each journey is encoded as a structured care plan with milestones, windows, completion semantics, dependencies, and escalation criteria. The plans are owned by clinical leadership for the journey type, version-controlled, reviewed annually.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Milestone-tracking pipeline with explicit state machines.** Each milestone has an explicit state machine. State transitions are driven by events from underlying systems and by patient-disclosed events from conversation. The pipeline is deterministic, not LLM-managed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Records-flow workflow as first-class architectural component.** The records-flow workflow has its own architectural box: requests, transmissions, confirmations, gap-detection. The workflow runs deterministically with consent-state checks. The assistant is the conversational surface for the workflow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Family-and-caregiver consent posture.** The assistant supports patient-designated caregivers as co-users where consent permits. The consent posture is encoded in the consent-record, refreshed periodically, revocable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-institutional information-flow integration.** The assistant operates in a multi-institutional reality. The information architecture accommodates EHR-internal data, HIE-mediated data, direct-connect-partner data, and patient-attested data with appropriate provenance tracking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Social-determinants overlay with care-navigation handoff.** The assistant integrates social-determinants signals where the institution has them and routes social-determinants concerns to care-navigation pathways.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every clinical-content reference, every milestone-state claim, every action confirmation is grounded in a cited source with retrieval timestamp and source-system preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the assistant is uncertain, when the patient's responses are ambiguous, when the conversation drifts toward clinical-judgment territory, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a person."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, attrition, milestone-completion rates, referral-completion rates, appointment-attendance rates, records-flow completion rates, escalation rates, citation-coverage rates, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, journey type, and social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any of the multiple integrated systems is unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble accessing the most current information; let me have a human coordinator follow up with you" with direct routing to the human-coordinator queue. The graceful-degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
